rComments: Simply the best prof. Caring, knowledge-abundant, explains everything clearly. The content may not be very easy though, lectures are engaging. The grade you'll receive is literally a fair payoff for your work. Definitely will take his classes again!

Professor Kim is a really amazing lecturer! He really knows the material upside down and backwards which makes his lectures super engaging. Plus he is very passionate about the material which also makes it easier to learn. The course content is undoubtedly difficult but Prof Kim makes it comprehensible!

Kim is an amazing professor, who really knows a lot about optogenetics. Besides, he is very kind and approachable guy, who is always there for his students. His choice of discussion topics was great, and I can surely say that this seminar was the most interesting course I've taken during my time at UofT.

Dr. Kim is an extremely friendly, approachable and knowledgeable man. I've had him for three classes and he's always very willing to answer questions thoroughly in class. He has a wealth of knowledge that he's very willing to share with those who are interested in learning it. Additionally, he's a pretty lenient and "chill" guy.

There's no skirting it: the material is hard. But I learned a ton! Kim knows so much about neuro. There was no question he couldn't answer. When he got excited about a topic, it was infectious. His slides were detailed but clear. I also liked our textbook's format. Bottom line:if you're into the subject and if you study hard, you'll learn a lot.
